aas_core.aas3_0.types.model

Interface IAdministrativeInformation

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IClass, IHasDataSpecification
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdministrativeInformation, EnhancedAdministrativeInformation

    public interface IAdministrativeInformation
extends IHasDataSpecification
    Administrative meta-information for an element like version information.

    Constraints:

    • Constraint AASd-005: If getVersion() is not specified then also getRevision() shall be unspecified. This means, a revision requires a version. If there is no version there is no revision neither. Revision is optional.

      • getTemplateId

        Optional<String> getTemplateId()
        Identifier of the template that guided the creation of the element.

        In case of a submodel the getTemplateId() is the identifier of the submodel template ID that guided the creation of the submodel

        The getTemplateId() is not relevant for validation in Submodels. For validation the Submodel.getSemanticId() shall be used.

        Usage of getTemplateId() is not restricted to submodel instances. So also the creation of submodel templates can be guided by another submodel template.
